{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Given the current capabilities of LLMs such as ChatGPT and GPT4, the zero-shot ability of these systems for a wide range of tasks, including NLG evaluation, has been investigated.",
    "Existing works have looked at using LLM to evaluate open-ended story generation and adversarial attacks (Chiang and Lee, 2023) and using ChatGPT to score the quality of texts along a certain axis (Wang et al., 2023; Kocmi and Federmann, 2023), demonstrating that ChatGPT can be used in a zero-shot setting and achieve reasonable performance.",
    "Pairwise comparative judgement (Thurstone, 1927) has been a popular approach of assessing candidates for exams, however where typically human assessors are used.",
    "Investigating the ability and application of pairwise comparisons via LLMs has been relatively underexplored, with concurrent work using pairwise rankings for information text retrieval (Qin et al., 2023) and separately for assessing LLM-based chat assistants on open-ended questions where outputs are compared to that of a baseline system (Chiang et al., 2023; Zheng et al., 2023).",
    "In this work, we investigate using LLM comparative judgements for NLG assessment."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Existing works have looked at using LLM to evaluate open-ended story generation and adversarial attacks (Chiang and Lee, 2023) and using ChatGPT to score the quality of texts along a certain axis (Wang et al., 2023; Kocmi and Federmann, 2023), demonstrating that ChatGPT can be used in a zero-shot setting and achieve reasonable performance.",
    "Pairwise comparative judgement (Thurstone, 1927) has been a popular approach of assessing candidates for exams, however where typically human assessors are used.",
    "Investigating the ability and application of pairwise comparisons via LLMs has been relatively underexplored, with concurrent work using pairwise rankings for information text retrieval (Qin et al., 2023) and separately for assessing LLM-based chat assistants on open-ended questions where outputs are compared to that of a baseline system (Chiang et al., 2023; Zheng et al., 2023)."
